06/05/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Corruption is widespread in Albania's public institutions, a study by the Institute for Research and Development Alternatives concluded on Wednesday (May 5th). According to the report, 91% of citizens believe that corruption is rampant in the public sector, with the health sector viewed as most corrupt. Of all 1,200 citizens polled, about 80% say it is very hard to get information from the courts, while 60% think that the media fights corruption the most. (Shekulli, Lajmifundit, Ora News, Top Channel - 05/05/10)
